.TH COMMAND * 2014-04-08 "SequoiaDB" "Sequoiadb sdb's Manual"
.ad l.ll 72.ce 1000
\fBdb.snapshot()\fR
.ce 0
.sp 2

.SH "NAME"

.sp 2
snapshot - It lists snapshots.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.sp 2

.sp 2

.sp 2
snapshot(\fBsnapType\fR,\fB[cond]\fR,\fB[sel]\fR,\fB[sort]\fR)
.SH "CATEGORY"

.sp 2

.sp 2
Sequoiadb
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

.sp 2
It lists snapshots. Snapshot is a kind of command used to get the
current status of system.
.sp 2
\fBsnapType (List)\fR
.br
       Snapshot type, the value of snapshot type is in the range
       from 0 to 7.
.sp 2
\fBcond (json object)\fR
.br
       Selection criteria, only to return snapshot information
       con field specifies the node or partition group to null,
       returns the entire snapshot information.
.sp 2
       \fBFormat\fR
.br
              The defination of the method "snapshot()" contains
              four fields: snapType, cond, sel, sort. The type of
              "snapType" is enumeration. Other fields are json
              objects. The format is as follow:
.br
              {"snapType":"<snapshot type>",["cond":"{"Field name
              1":{"operation 1":"value 1"},"Field name
              2":{"Operation 2":"value 2"}...}"]}
.sp 2

.sp 2
\fBNote: \fR
.sp 2
   *  The value of snapType is in the range from 0 to 7.
.sp 2
   *  The parameter "sel" is a json object. The value of field
   name is specified as null string. It is defined as: {"Field
   name 1":"value 1","Field name 2":"value 2",...}.If the records
   contain the specified field names, the values are invalid. If
   the records don't contain specified fields, it returns
   "{"Field name 1":"value 1", "Field name 2":"value 2"}".
.sp 2
   *  If the value of a field is in the type of array. We invoke
   the elements in it through "." and double quotations.
.SH "Examples"

.sp 2
Set the value of "snapType" as 0:
.sp 2
db.snapshot(0)
.sp 2
Returns context snapshot of the entire cluster:
.sp 2
{
.br
  "SessionID": "vmsvr1-cent-x64-1:11820:22",
.br
  "Contexts": [
.br
    {
.br
      "ContextID": 8,
.br
      "Type": "DUMP",
.br
      "Description": "BufferSize:0",
.br
      "DataRead": 0,
.br
      "IndexRead": 0,
.br
      "QueryTimeSpent": 0,
.br
      "StartTimestamp": "2013-12-28-16.07.59.146399"
.br
    }
.br
  ]
.br
}
.br
